arm_group.description: MALE PATIENTS BEFORE UDS WITH DIFFICULT CATHETERIZATION

brief_summary.textblock:
A report of a technique for insertion a soft urodynamic catheter into the bladder, when
      urethral obstruction causes the catheter to bend and fold over itself at the resistance
      site.

clinical_study.brief_title: Tiemann Mounted Urodynamic Catheter Technique for Difficult Bladder Catheterization

detailed_description.textblock:
The urodynamic catheter is mounted on a 12F Coudé tip Tiemann catheter, which then carries
      the tip of the urodynamic catheter beyond the obstruction site into the bladder.

      The Tiemann catheter-mounted urodynamic catheter technique can serve as a suitable option to
      insert a urodynamic catheter into the bladder in all male patients in whom it fails due to
      kinking.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

        - MEN THAT UNDERWENT URODYNAMIC STUDY EVALUATION BETWEEN 6/2011 TO 9/2013

        Exclusion Criteria:

        NONE

        -

clinical_study.official_title: RETROSPECTIVE STUDY ABOUT A TECHNIQUE OF INSERTION OF TIEMANN MOUNTED URODYNAMIC CATHETER FOR DIFFICULT BLADDER CATHETERIZATION IN MALES
